<div class="modal-backdrop" id="help-modal" hidden role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="help-title">
  <div class="modal">
    <div class="modal-header">
      <img id="jake-headshot-modal" alt="Jake Skidmore">
      <div>
        <h2 id="help-title">Ask Jake</h2>
        <div class="from">SLD Renderer — quick guide</div>
      </div>
      <div class="spacer"></div>
      <button class="close" id="btn-close-help" aria-label="Close">Ã—</button>
    </div>
    <div class="modal-body">
      <h3>1. Load a diagram</h3>
      <p>Drop an <code>sld_input.json</code> file onto the left panel, or click the drop zone to browse. The diagram will render on the <strong>Diagram</strong> tab and the device list will populate on the <strong>Components &amp; Specs</strong> tab.</p>

      <h3>2. View the diagram</h3>
      <p>The <strong>Diagram</strong> tab shows the laid-out SLD. The summary panel on the left lists device counts, bus counts, and any flagged issues (cycles or required-input devices).</p>

      <h3>3. Edit or delete components</h3>
      <p>Switch to the <strong>Components &amp; Specs</strong> tab. Each device is its own card. Click the <strong>pencil</strong> to edit:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Name</strong> — the label shown on the diagram block.</li>
        <li><strong>Specs</strong> — comma-separated rating items (e.g. <code>2000A, 480V, LSIG</code>). These appear under the device name as chips.</li>
        <li><strong>Bus position</strong> — a number that orders siblings left-to-right on the same row. Lower numbers go left. Leave blank to let the layout engine decide.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Click <strong>Save</strong> on the card to push the change to the SLD, or the <strong>trash</strong> icon to remove the component entirely (any references to it are unlinked).</p>

      <h3>4. Export</h3>
      <p>Use the top-right buttons to <strong>Download SVG</strong>, <strong>Download PNG</strong>, or <strong>Print / PDF</strong>. These reflect the most recent render — save your edits first.</p>

      <div class="signoff">Anything missing? Ping me and I'll fix it. — Jake</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

